## Design System Constraints

These constraints apply to every component on this dashboard. Consistency with the existing platform visual language is non-negotiable.

### General rules

- No emojis anywhere on the dashboard — not in headers, cards, buttons, or loading states
- No decorative iconography — functional icons only where they already exist in the platform design system
- No new colors — use the existing platform palette exclusively for backgrounds, borders, text, and status indicators
- No bold evaluative language in UI chrome — section labels and affordance text are neutral and descriptive

### Typography

- Section labels: small uppercase with increased letter-spacing, muted color — consistent with existing tab section labels
- Card headlines: medium weight, readable at a glance
- Body text: regular weight, standard line height — the synthesis content needs to breathe
- Metric values in the vitals strip: larger numeral weight — the same treatment as the existing vitals strip

### Cards and containers

- Subtle border and light background fill — consistent with the existing insight card style throughout the platform
- Consistent internal padding across all card types
- No heavy shadow or dramatic elevation — this is a professional information-dense dashboard, not a consumer card interface

### Layout rhythm

- Standard horizontal page padding applied consistently across all sections
- Section spacing should create clear visual separation between narrative beats without feeling sparse
- The three-column Operating Realities layout is the most structurally distinct section — keep its internal card spacing consistent with the two-column At-a-Glance grid above it
- Sections that are full-width prose (Executive Headline, Executive Summary, Synthesis Statement) should have a slightly narrower max-width than card-grid sections to improve line length readability

### Responsive behavior

- Business Vitals Strip: 6-column on desktop, 3x2 grid on tablet, 2x3 grid on mobile
- Agency At-a-Glance: 2x2 grid on desktop, 2x2 on tablet, 1x4 stacked on mobile
- Cross-Dimensional Signals: single column at all breakpoints — these are already full-width cards
- Operating Realities: 3-column on desktop, single column on tablet and mobile
- CTA section: single column at all breakpoints

