## Element 4 — Agency At-a-Glance

### Rationale

This section is the bridge between the system-level executive summary and the cross-dimensional signals. Before the founder reads what the dimensions reveal in relationship to each other, they benefit from a quick reorientation to what each dimension said on its own terms. This is especially valuable for founders who moved quickly through the sub-tabs and may not have fully absorbed each synthesis.

The critical design decision here is what *not* to include. The previous version of this section had directional status indicators — labels like Aligned, Pressure, Watch, Healthy — that applied evaluative judgment to each dimension. These have been removed intentionally. The At-a-Glance section is not an evaluation layer. It is a navigable portrait layer. The cards exist so the founder can re-read the synthesis signals and optionally go deeper into the three beats for each dimension. Adding status labels would tip the section from observational to evaluative, which contradicts the platform's core voice principle.

The pop-out behavior is the right interaction model here because the beat content is supplementary depth, not primary content. A founder who already remembers what their delivery architecture synthesis said doesn't need to expand that card. A founder who wants to revisit it before reading the cross-dimensional signals can. Optional depth, not mandatory reading.

**Section label:** `AGENCY AT-A-GLANCE` — small uppercase, muted

**Layout:** Two-by-two grid — Market Footprint and Economic Foundation in the top row, Revenue Model and Delivery Architecture in the bottom row

**Component:** Four dimension cards, each expandable into a pop-out modal or side drawer

**Data sources — all deterministic from view:**

Each card uses fields prefixed by its dimension identifier:

Market Footprint (`mf_`):
- `mf_synthesis_signal` — card body text
- `mf_beat_1_headline`, `mf_beat_1` — pop-out content
- `mf_beat_2_headline`, `mf_beat_2` — pop-out content
- `mf_beat_3_headline`, `mf_beat_3` — pop-out content

Economic Foundation (`ef_`):
- `ef_synthesis_signal`, `ef_beat_1_headline`, `ef_beat_1`, `ef_beat_2_headline`, `ef_beat_2`, `ef_beat_3_headline`, `ef_beat_3`

Revenue Model (`rm_`):
- `rm_synthesis_signal`, `rm_beat_1_headline`, `rm_beat_1`, `rm_beat_2_headline`, `rm_beat_2`, `rm_beat_3_headline`, `rm_beat_3`

Delivery Architecture (`da_`):
- `da_synthesis_signal`, `da_beat_1_headline`, `da_beat_1`, `da_beat_2_headline`, `da_beat_2`, `da_beat_3_headline`, `da_beat_3`

**Closed card state:**
- Dimension name as the card title (Market Footprint, Economic Foundation, Revenue Model, Delivery Architecture)
- `synthesis_signal` as the card body text
- "View Full Analysis" as a subtle text link or expand affordance at the bottom of the card
- No status indicators, no color-coded badges, no directional labels

**Pop-out expanded state:**
- Modal or side drawer — side drawer preferred if it fits platform patterns, as it keeps the dashboard visible in the background
- Modal title: dimension name
- Three beats in sequence: beat headline in medium weight followed by beat body text in regular weight
- Close control (X or Done) to return to dashboard
- Dismissible by clicking outside the modal area

**Behavior:**
- All four cards render simultaneously on dashboard complete
- If `synthesis_signal` is null for any card, show a soft prompt in the card body: "Complete and synthesize your [dimension name] tab to see this analysis"
- Only one pop-out open at a time
- Pop-out state does not persist on page refresh

**Design:**
- Subtle border and light background fill consistent with existing insight card style
- Card internal padding consistent with other card components on the platform
- Equal height cards within each row — content should not cause individual cards to be taller than their row partner
- Two-column grid on desktop and tablet, single column on mobile (stacked in the order: Market Footprint, Economic Foundation, Revenue Model, Delivery Architecture)
- No emojis or decorative icons in card headers

