## Element 7 — Synthesis Statement

### Rationale

The synthesis statement is the emotional and intellectual close of the analytical journey. The executive headline at the top was the TLDR — before the detail. The synthesis statement is the crystallization — after the detail. The founder has now absorbed the dimensional portraits, the cross-dimensional signals, and the structural implications. They have earned the right to receive the single most resonant structural truth that emerges from all of it, stated cleanly.

The contrast with the executive headline is important. The headline was a so-what before the founder had the full picture. The synthesis statement is the same quality of observation, but it lands differently because the founder has just spent time with everything that supports it. It should feel like arrival — the moment when everything they read clicks into a single coherent understanding of their own business.

Two to four sentences is the right constraint. Longer and it starts to feel like a conclusion section rather than a closing statement. The empowerment comes from clarity, not from volume. A founder should finish reading it and feel like they understand something about their business they couldn't quite articulate before this moment.

**Section label:** `SYNTHESIS` — small uppercase, muted

**Layout:** Full width

**Component:** Prose text block — no card container

**Data source:** `synthesis_statement` from view — GPT return field

**Behavior:**
- Renders as standalone text — no card container, no background fill
- Prose only — no bullet points, no subheadings within the block
- Positioned after Operating Realities and before the Next Steps CTA

**Design:**
- Typographic treatment slightly elevated relative to body text — this is the closing statement of the dashboard and should feel like it carries more weight than the executive summary above it
- Consider a subtle top border above this section — a thin full-width rule that signals "here is the close" — or simply increased top margin to give it visual breathing room from the Operating Realities section
- Constrained max-width consistent with the Executive Summary above — these two prose elements should share the same visual container width for cohesion
- Bottom margin before the CTA section should be generous — this statement needs to land before the founder is directed anywhere else

**Design recommendation:** The synthesis statement and the executive headline are bookends — they frame the entire experience. Consider a subtle visual treatment that echoes them to each other — the same type size, the same max-width, the same absence of a card container. A founder scrolling the page should feel the structural symmetry between the opening and the close.

